article.headline: NC Central beats Florida A&M 81-63
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Dante Holmes had 19 points and eight rebounds, Patrick Cole scored 17 and North Carolina Central eased past Florida A&M for an 81-63 win Monday night. Jeremiah Ingram added 11 points and C.J. Wiggins had 10 for the Eagles (8-14, 3-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). NCCU built a 43-27 halftime lead and stretched it to as many as 19 in the second half. The Eagles snapped a three-game losing streak while the Rattlers lost their third in a row. Isaiah Omoregie scored 16 points and Malcolm Bernard added 15 for Florida A&M (6-15, 2-6).
